[
    {
        "content": "<p>Often in Lean3 it is convenient to use <code>simp at ⊢ h</code>. The <code>⊢ </code> seems to be unacceptable in lean4. Do we have some way to do this in lean4?</p>",
        "id": 359495469,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1684443379
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've missed this too.</p>",
        "id": 359495505,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1684443394
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not a total solution, but how about <code>simp_all</code>?</p>",
        "id": 359495634,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1684443439
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, we can still do <code>simp at *</code>, which does less than <code>simp_all</code>, but I still want to have control over what I simplify.</p>",
        "id": 359495827,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1684443497
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We also don't have <code>dsimp_all</code></p>",
        "id": 359495894,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1684443523
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I had noticed that also, but if you change the order, it works: <code>(d)simp at h ⊢</code>.</p>",
        "id": 359499426,
        "sender_full_name": "Joël Riou",
        "timestamp": 1684444714
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The <code>at</code> location syntax requires that <code>⊢</code> comes last</p>",
        "id": 359501038,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1684445359
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Aha! Okay thanks!</p>",
        "id": 359501710,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1684445628
    }
]